    <div style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
      <span style="color:var(--text-dim)">Memory     </span>
      <span class="arrow">──</span>
      <span class="box box-magenta">memory.py (.gondola_memory.json)</span>
      <span class="arrow"> ── </span>
      <span class="box box-magenta">ProjectIndex (.gondola_index.json)</span>
      <span class="arrow"> ── </span>
      <span class="box box-magenta">KnowledgeOps</span>
    </div>

    <div>
      <span style="color:var(--text-dim)">Shadow Git </span>
      <span class="arrow">──</span>
      <span class="box box-magenta">_gondola_shadow branch</span>
      <span class="arrow"> ── </span>
      <span class="box box-magenta">Necromancer commits (thought checkpoints)</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <br>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">AgentState</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Per-session dataclass tracking turn count, files read/written, tool call history with dedup detection, exploration budget, reasoning enforcement, and staged transaction support.</div>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span class="tag cyan">agent_state.py</span>
        <span class="tag green">@dataclass</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">ContextManager</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Token-aware context builder. Compresses large tool results by omitting the middle of files, grouping file listings, and capping search results. Injects truncation notices so the model knows what was cut.</div>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span class="tag cyan">context_manager.py</span>
        <span class="tag yellow">20K char limit</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">PersistenceManager</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Uses low-level git plumbing (<code>hash-object</code>, <code>commit-tree</code>, <code>update-ref</code>) to write Necromancer checkpoint commits to <code>_gondola_shadow</code> without checking out the branch.</div>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span class="tag cyan">persistence.py</span>
        <span class="tag magenta">_gondola_shadow</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">UndeadOpsMixin (Tree-sitter)</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Lazily-initialized Tree-sitter parsers for Python and JS/TS. Provides <code>get_skeleton()</code>, <code>symbol_jump()</code> via ctags, and <code>inspect_type()</code> via Jedi — stateless code analysis.</div>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span class="tag cyan">undead_ops.py</span>
        <span class="tag blue">Tree-sitter</span>
        <span class="tag blue">Jedi</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">CombinedTools</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Single class that inherits all tool mixins via Python MRO: File, Code, Undead (Tree-sitter), Git, Web, Shell, Test, Image, Batch, Knowledge — one unified interface for the API layer.</div>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span class="tag cyan">tools/__init__.py</span>
        <span class="tag green">MRO composition</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Tool Schema Validation</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Every tool has a typed JSON schema in <code>schema.py</code>. Pre-flight <code>validate_tool_args()</code> catches bad args from cheap models before execution — coerces strings/booleans, rejects wrong types.</div>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span class="tag cyan">tools/schema.py</span>
        <span class="tag red">pre-flight check</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

