<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ SAFETY ═══ -->
<section class="section" id="safety">
  <div class="section-label">05 — Safety &amp; Rules</div>
  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">🛡️</span>RiskAnalyzer &amp; Enforcement Rules</h2>

  <div class="warn-box">
    <strong>Hard Block:</strong> Any edit scoring above the model's threshold (default 100) is blocked with an explanation. The agent must re-read the file and re-attempt with a safer approach.
  </div>

  <h3 style="font-size:14px;color:var(--cyan);font-family:Consolas,monospace;margin-bottom:14px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;">Risk Scoring Factors</h3>
  <table class="risk-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Risk Factor</th>
        <th>Score Added</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="risk-name">FILE NEVER READ</span></td>
        <td><span class="risk-score critical">+100</span></td>
        <td>Editing a file the agent has never read — critical blindspot</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="risk-name">EXTERNAL MODIFICATION</span></td>
        <td><span class="risk-score critical">+80</span></td>
        <td>File hash changed on disk since agent last read it</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="risk-name">CHANGES FUNCTION SIGNATURE</span></td>
        <td><span class="risk-score high">+60</span></td>
        <td>Function definitions differ between search and replace blocks</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="risk-name">LARGE DELETION (&gt;20 lines)</span></td>
        <td><span class="risk-score high">+50</span></td>
        <td>Net deletion exceeds 20 lines</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="risk-name">STALE READ (&gt;5 turns ago)</span></td>
        <td><span class="risk-score medium">+40</span></td>
        <td>File was read more than 5 turns ago — may be outdated</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="risk-name">CLASS DEFINITION CHANGE</span></td>
        <td><span class="risk-score medium">+30</span></td>
        <td>Modifies a class definition line</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="risk-name">MEDIUM DELETION (10–20 lines)</span></td>
        <td><span class="risk-score medium">+25</span></td>
        <td>Net deletion between 10 and 20 lines</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="risk-name">IMPORT CHANGES</span></td>
        <td><span class="risk-score low">+20</span></td>
        <td>Adds, removes, or modifies import statements</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <br>
  <h3 style="font-size:14px;color:var(--cyan);font-family:Consolas,monospace;margin-bottom:14px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;">Model Risk Tolerance Thresholds</h3>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Claude Opus / GLM</div>
      <div class="card-desc" style="font-family:Consolas,monospace;">Block threshold: <span style="color:var(--green);">120</span><br>Highest tolerance — these models rarely need blocking.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Claude Sonnet / Default</div>
      <div class="card-desc" style="font-family:Consolas,monospace;">Block threshold: <span style="color:var(--cyan);">100</span><br>Standard. Blocked on FILE_NEVER_READ alone.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Qwen Models</div>
      <div class="card-desc" style="font-family:Consolas,monospace;">Block threshold: <span style="color:var(--yellow);">90</span><br>Slightly more cautious — can be overconfident.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Llama / Maverick</div>
      <div class="card-desc" style="font-family:Consolas,monospace;">Block threshold: <span style="color:var(--orange);">80</span><br>More cautious — sometimes guesses content.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Groq Models</div>
      <div class="card-desc" style="font-family:Consolas,monospace;">Block threshold: <span style="color:var(--red);">70</span><br>Most cautious — fast but least accurate with edits.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <br>
  <h3 style="font-size:14px;color:var(--cyan);font-family:Consolas,monospace;margin-bottom:14px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;">Loop Prevention Rules</h3>
  <ul class="rule-list">
    <li>
      <span class="rule-icon">📊</span>
      <span class="rule-text"><strong>Exploration Budget:</strong> Max 8 exploration actions (read/search/list/map) per task. At budget, next action must be a write/edit or <code>done()</code>. Each productive action replenishes 3 exploration credits.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="rule-icon">🔁</span>
      <span class="rule-text"><strong>Pattern Loop Detection:</strong> If the last 2 tool calls match the 2 calls before them (same tool types), a loop warning is injected. If the last 3 exact call signatures match the 3 before them, the agent is forced to call <code>done()</code>.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="rule-icon">🗂️</span>
      <span class="rule-text"><strong>Duplicate Read Guard:</strong> <code>AgentState.record_file_read()</code> detects if the exact same file content is being read twice. Returns <em>"DUPLICATE: You already read this file at turn N. Content unchanged."</em></span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="rule-icon">💬</span>
      <span class="rule-text"><strong>Silent Operation Warning:</strong> If the model makes 2+ consecutive tool calls without any explanatory text, a warning is injected: <em>"SILENT OPERATION WARNING — briefly explain what you're doing."</em></span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="rule-icon">⏱️</span>
      <span class="rule-text"><strong>Turn Limit Enforcement:</strong> Each model has a <code>max_agent_turns</code> cap (default 50 for elite models). At the limit, <code>force_done_at_max</code> injects a final system message and calls <code>done()</code>.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="rule-icon">🔍</span>
      <span class="rule-text"><strong>Checkpoint Injections:</strong> System reminder messages at turns 5, 10, and 15 prompt the agent to evaluate progress and complete if sufficient context is gathered.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="rule-icon">🚫</span>
      <span class="rule-text"><strong>Placeholder Detection:</strong> <code>write_file</code> blocks content containing patterns like <code>"&lt;!-- content from above --&gt;"</code>, <code>"// see above"</code>, or suspiciously short code files (&lt;20 chars).</span>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

