  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">💰</span>Session Cost Tracking</h2>

  <div class="info-box">
    Venice returns live balance headers after every API call. Gondola captures these, computes a per-session delta, and persists the current balance for the next session. All cost data is emitted in the final <code>done</code> SSE event.
  </div>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--green);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Balance Headers</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Venice response headers <code>x-venice-balance-usd</code> and <code>x-venice-balance-vcu</code> are extracted after every streaming response. The latest values are stored in memory and persisted via <code>memory.save_balance()</code>.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--cyan);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Delta Calculation</div>
      <div class="card-desc">A baseline is captured at request start (<code>baseline_usd = last_balance_usd</code>). After the response: <code>cost_usd = baseline_usd − curr_usd</code>. Negative deltas (deposits) are ignored.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--yellow);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Session Summary</div>
      <div class="card-desc">The <code>done</code> SSE event carries: <code>total_cost_usd</code>, <code>total_cost_vcu</code>, <code>tokens_in</code>, <code>tokens_out</code>, <code>session_duration</code>, <code>turn_count</code>, <code>model_id</code>, <code>provider</code>. Powers the Session Stats panel in Daft UI.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--blue);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Balance API</div>
      <div class="card-desc"><code>GET /api/balance</code> returns the last-known formatted balance: <code>{"usd": "$X.XXXX", "vcu": "YYYYVCU"}</code>. Displayed in the Daft UI title bar between model name and READY status.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
